ImmuneErrorRadar implements a falsification-first research workflow for biomedical
hypothesis stress-testing. It is not a medical device, diagnostic tool, treatment
recommendation system, clinical decision-support product, or wet-laboratory validation.

The project uses a Vraimony-inspired evidence receipt discipline: hash-first,
portable, replayable, and claim-bounded. References to Vraimony, ERF-inspired
receipts, or the ImmuneErrorRadar falsification protocol describe documentation
and reproducibility methodology; they do not imply clinical validation or proof of
biology.

Data policy: repository artifacts should avoid redistributing controlled or
third-party expression matrices unless the applicable source license allows it.
Hash-only fixtures and regeneration instructions are preferred for public release.
